**Hands-On Commands**
- `kubectl describe pod <pod-name> -n <namespace>` → View reason for CrashLoopBackOff.
- `kubectl logs <pod-name> -n <namespace> --previous` → See last crash logs.
- `kubectl get events -n <namespace> --sort-by=.metadata.creationTimestamp | tail -20` → Latest events.
- `kubectl top pod <pod-name> -n <namespace>` → Check CPU/mem pressure.
